3 SECTION 3. NEW AND VACANT FTE POOL - LIMITATION - TRANSFER REQUEST. The
4 parks and recreation department may not spend funds appropriated in the new and vacant FTE
5 pool line item in section 1 of this Act, but may request the office of management and budget to
6 transfer funds from the new and vacant FTE pool line item to other line items with salaries and
7 wages in accordance with the guidelines and reporting provisions included in House Bill
8 No. 1015, as approved by the sixty-ninth legislative assembly.
9 SECTION 4. ADDITIONAL INCOME - APPROPRIATION - REPORTING. In addition to the
10 amounts appropriated in section 1 of this Act, any additional federal or special funds that
11 become available are appropriated to the parks and recreation department, for the biennium
12 beginning July 1, 2025, and ending June 30, 2027. The department shall report any additional
13 income under this section to the office of management and budget and the legislative council.
14 SECTION 5. TRANSFER - GAME AND FISH DEPARTMENT TO PARKS AND
15 RECREATION DEPARTMENT - GAME AND FISH OPERATING FUND - BOAT RAMP
16 OPERATION AND MAINTENANCE. The sum of $122,000, or so much of the sum as may be
17 necessary, included in the park operations and maintenance line item in subdivision 1 of
18 section 1 of this Act, is from the game and fish operating fund, or federal or other funds
19 available to the game and fish department, which must be transferred to the parks and
20 recreation department for maintenance, operating, and extraordinary repairs expenses relating
21 to boat ramps at state parks, for the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, and ending June 30,
22 2027.
